## Bug Description

`clearThreadLocals()` unconditionally sets `inheritableThreadLocals` to null for the entire thread, not just clearing entries loaded by the target ClassLoader. This breaks any other application or system code that uses inheritable thread locals on that thread.

## Location
- File: `jplatform-classloader/src/main/java/org/flossware/jplatform/classloader/ClassLoaderCleanupUtil.java`
- Lines: 144-146

## Problematic Code

```java
// Also clean inheritableThreadLocals
Field inheritableThreadLocalsField = Thread.class.getDeclaredField("inheritableThreadLocals");
inheritableThreadLocalsField.setAccessible(true);
inheritableThreadLocalsField.set(thread, null);  // WIPES OUT ALL inheritable thread locals!
```

The code correctly filters `threadLocals` by ClassLoader (lines 125-139), but then unconditionally nukes ALL `inheritableThreadLocals` regardless of which ClassLoader loaded them.

## Example Demonstrating the Bug

```java
// Setup: System code sets an inheritable thread local
InheritableThreadLocal<String> systemThreadLocal = new InheritableThreadLocal<>();
systemThreadLocal.set("important-system-data");

// Application cleanup runs
ClassLoaderCleanupUtil cleanup = new ClassLoaderCleanupUtil("my-app", appClassLoader);
cleanup.cleanupThreadLocals();

// System code breaks - inheritable thread local is now null!
String data = systemThreadLocal.get();  // null - data was lost!
```

